      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAPERBOY (7) is a fast beginner who has shown good improvement at his last two starts, breaking through last time at Murray Bridge Straight over 300m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Expected to be right there at the finish again. CHAOTIC BOY (2) goes very well this trip starting 12 times for five wins and four minors. Below best last time at Angle Park (20.34) in a Grade 5, finishing a 6 length fifth. Makes strong appeal on best. SIR RICO (1) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has been in the money the last six starts, the latest when second (18.31) at Mt Gambier. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. Leading player again. TERRIFIC LUCY (4) jumps at a shorter distance and still warrants respect.",
